SAM (Sales and marketing) 
Description : This project is mainly used by person in marketing, sales and management of healthcare. There are six main areas that have developed, and they include Application Management, Campaigns, Opportunities, Leads, Accounts, and Contacts.  
Application Management : - Masters, Users, Roles, Customization and Logging
Accounts : - The account is the area where a person would add/edit/lookup accounts. Accounts consist of entities as it relates to businesses such as a hospital or a physician group practice. 
Contacts : -The contacts area is where a person wills add/edit/lookup contacts. A contact consists of information on individual people. 
Opportunities : -This area is where a user will add/edit/lookup opportunities. An opportunity is when the sales team finds a contact that says they want to buy something.
Leads : -This area is where a user will add/edit/lookup leads. A lead is when we think an account or contact may want something.
Once the lead is worked on by a SAM user, it could turn into an Opportunity. 
SAM user have actions taken on lead or opportunity such as email, send proposal etc.
There is logging of what a SAM user change or move through out web.
Environment : C#, Visual Studio 2010 , Dev Express for web, Sql Server, VSS. 
Role Played : Team Member.

Transriter Client Portal

IDictaFlow
Description : A mobile capture application will capture a physician's voice dictation via a mobile device.	  Specifically, it will be used by iOS devices such as iPhone and iPod.
This project includes : 
A physician captures voice dictation via mobile device. 
While dictating, he/she may play, stop, pause or continue dictating.
When he/she finishes dictation, the dictation is sent to Transriter System for transcription.
 Environment : C#, REST Service, Visual Studio 2008 , Sql Server, XCode and Objective C. 
Role Played : Coding and designing Mobile application using Xcode using Objective C.
Transriter Capture
Description : Transriter Capture (Application) will handle dictation files made on hand held dictation devices by physicians. The application has the following scope : 
It will copy dictation files from handheld device to a PC.
It will verify for copied files on PC. It will make sure all the files are copied to PC successfully.
If verification is true, then it will delete all the files from handheld device.
Then it will transfer all the files to Transriter System from the PC.
Environment : C#, Visual Studio 2010 , Dev Express for windows, VSS, WCF Service.
